                                    </div>
                                    
                                    
                                    </div>
                                </a>
                            
                            
                              <!-- Body -->
                              <div class="media-body article-info bucket-margin margin-24-bottom clearfix">
                                  <a class="unskinned display-inline-block eyebrow-link margin-4-bottom" href="https://time.com/history/">
                                    <div class="category heading-eyebrow">
                                      History
                                    </div>
                                  </a>
                            
                                <h3 class="headline heading-3 heading-content margin-8-bottom media-heading">
                                  <a href="https://time.com/5815551/passover-easter-coronavirus-history/">
                                      Celebrating Easter and Passover During Past Pandemics
                                  </a>
                                </h3>
                            
                                <div class="article-info-extended">
                            
                                </div>
                            
                            
                              </div>
                            </article>
                                      <article
                              class="partial tile media image-top  type-"
                              data-crop="marquee_large_2x"
                              data-headline-style="heading-content"
                            >
                                <!-- Image Media -->
                                <a class="media-img margin-16-bottom" href="https://time.com/5815693/church-of-jesus-christ-of-latter-day-saints-conference-livestream/">
                                    <div
                                      class="component lazy-image  marquee_large_2x
                                        
                                        
                                        "
                                      data-high-density="true"
                                      data-src="https://api.time.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/church-of-jesus-christ-of-latter-day-saints-conference-livestream.jpg?quality&#x3D;85&amp;w&#x3D;600"
                                      data-crop="marquee_large_2x"
                                      data-alt=""
                                      data-title=""
                                      data-shop-image="false"
                                          
                                      
                                    >
                                    
                                    <noscript>
                                      <div class="inner-container">
                                        <img src="https://api.time.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/church-of-jesus-christ-of-latter-day-saints-conference-livestream.jpg?quality&#x3D;85&amp;w&#x3D;600" alt="" title="">
                                      </div>
                                    </noscript>
                                    
                                    <div class="inner-container js-inner-container ">
                                    </div>
                                    
                                    
                                    </div>
                                </a>
                            
                            
                              <!-- Body -->
                              <div class="media-body article-info bucket-margin margin-24-bottom clearfix">
                                  <a class="unskinned display-inline-block eyebrow-link margin-4-bottom" href="https://time.com/us/">
                                    <div class="category heading-eyebrow">
                                      U.S.
                                    </div>
                                  </a>
                            
                                <h3 class="headline heading-3 heading-content margin-8-bottom media-heading">
                                  <a href="https://time.com/5815693/church-of-jesus-christ-of-latter-day-saints-conference-livestream/">
                                      Mormon Church Livestreams Annual Conference
                                  </a>
                                </h3>
                            
                                <div class="article-info-extended">
                            
                                </div>
                            
                            
                              </div>
                            </article>
                          </div>
                <p>Our culture has downgraded the Christmas stories into sweet little songs and primary-school Nativity plays. But the birth of a baby who will inherit &#8220;the throne of his ancestor David&#8221; &mdash;as the angel says to Mary in Luke 1:32&mdash;announces the start of a revolution. Nothing will ever be the same again. In Israel&rsquo;s scriptures, David already ruled over the Twelve Tribes, but the Psalms and Prophets insisted that his ultimate successor would rule over the whole world. Anyone claiming David&rsquo;s kingdom is throwing down a challenge to the rulers of the world, whether in the first century or the twenty-first.</p>
                <p>But what sort of a challenge? We are so scared of &#8220;theocracy&#8221; (think: mad clerics bullying people into submission) that the thought of Jesus and his followers posing a real-life &#8220;challenge&#8221; is enough to send people back to the anodyne Christmas carols. The question of &#8220;theocracy,&#8221; (literally, the rule of God), however, turns on <em>which God it is we&rsquo;re talking about</em>. And here Matthew and Luke, starting with their Christmas stories, are clear. Their accounts of Jesus, right through to his <a href="https://time.com/5712369/crucifixion-religious-history/">cruel death</a> at the hands of the Roman imperial power, are saying, from a hundred different angles, <em>This is what it looks like when the real God comes to the rescue</em>. They echo the ancient biblical stories about Israel&rsquo;s God: the God who made the world in the first place; the one who heard his people&rsquo;s cry and came to rescue them through Moses; the one who always wanted to come and live in amongst his people and through them to renew and restore his whole creation.</p>
                <p>The stories that begin at Christmas end with Jesus&rsquo; followers sent into the world to launch a new way of being human; a new kind of power; the divine power of self-giving love. Once we put Christmas back into its proper historical context we might just find that Christmas could reshape our own historical context. God knows we need it: the homeless asylum seekers, yes, and the rest of us too.</p>
                
                
                  <div
                     id="ad-300x250_320x480_LL_m_2" 
                    data-tgxtrack="true" data-tgxtargeting="%7B%7D" data-tgxupdatecorrelator="true" data-tgxlazy="200"
                    class="ad ad-container ad-wrapper type-300x250;320x480 instream-ad mobile-ad"
                    data-dimensions="300x250;320x480" role="complementary" aria-hidden="true">
                  </div>
                
                
                  <div
                     id="ad-728x90_LL_td_2" 
                    data-tgxtargeting="%7B%7D" data-tgxlazy="200"
                    class="ad ad-container ad-wrapper type-728x90 instream-ad tablet-ad desktop-ad x2"
                    data-dimensions="728x90" role="complementary" aria-hidden="true">
